# Benchmark timing (hard policy)

**Each benchmark measurement budget is 60 seconds wall time, never more.**

- Applies to transfer-matrix, opt-ablation, and network-bench repeat loops (`sum(rep.wallMs) < 60_000` per workload Ã— system).
- Default and maximum `targetMs` / `NEARBYTES_TRANSFER_TARGET_MS` / `bench.targetMs` = **60000**. Values above are **clamped** in `scripts/lib/bench-timing.mjs`.
- Do **not** add `NEARBYTES_PAPER_BENCH_FULL` or multi-minute targets. `yarn bench:paper` uses the same 60s cap.
- Single slow trials (e.g. WAN 128 MiB) may use one rep when one rep exceeds 60s â€” that is expected.
- **Local loopback default** is *sustained* mode (`128MiB_sustained_20s`, `4MiB_sustained_20s`): each rep loops transfers until â‰¥20 s wall on a warm pair (3 reps â‰ˆ 60 s budget). Micro single-shot rows remain via `--micro` or `NEARBYTES_TRANSFER_MICRO=1`. Sustained rows also report `goodputWireMbps` (firstâ†’last wire byte window).
